```

## Accessibility Checklist

- [ ] Color contrast WCAG AA (4.5:1)
- [ ] Visible focus states
- [ ] Min 44x44px touch targets
- [ ] Proper ARIA labels
- [ ] Keyboard navigation
- [ ] Screen reader friendly

## Component Breakdown Example

```markdown
# SocialMediaPost Component

## Sub-components:
1. PostHeader (Avatar, Author, Timestamp, Menu)
2. PostContent (Text, Images, Link preview)
3. PostActions (Like, Comment, Share, Save)
4. PostComments (Comment list, Comment input)

## Props:
- post: Post object
- onLike: () => void
- onComment: (text: string) => void
- showComments: boolean
```

## Best Practices

### Do's ✅
- Break down into reusable components
- Design for multiple states (loading, error, empty)
- Consider responsive layouts
- Follow accessibility guidelines
- Document component specs

### Don'ts ❌
- Create monolithic components
- Hardcode values
- Ignore edge cases
- Forget loading/error states

